text: thumb|Jūshiyama in Aichi Prefecture thumb|former Jūshiyama Village Hall was a village located in Ama District, Aichi Prefecture, Japan. As of 2003, the village had an estimated population of 5,687 and a density of 570.41 persons per km². The total area was 9.97 km². On April 1, 2006, Jūshiyama was merged into the former town of Yatomi to create the city of Yatomi. ==External links== * Yatomi official website Category:Dissolved municipalities of Aichi Prefecture Category:Yatomi, Aichi
